⚠️ | QUICK STAT

Atlético Madrid have only lost two LaLiga matches since the World Cup:

🔴⚪️ 0–1 Barcelona (8 January)
🔴⚪️ 0–1 Barcelona (23 April)

Diego Simeone is now winless in 16 (!) visits to Camp Nou as Atleti manager.

#BarcaAtleti https://t.co/bjg159dpo2

🏴󠁧󠁢󠁥󠁮󠁧󠁿 | Brighton (6) 0–0 (7) Manchester United

There were no goals in the entire 120' at Wembley, with the two sides eventually going to the shootout, where Solly March was the only player to miss a penalty.

This now means there will be a Manchester derby in the #FACup final! 🤩 https://t.co/oIkH6YIGkK

🇮🇹 | Juventus 0–1 Napoli

After midweek disappointment, I Partenopei bounced back in perfect fashion thanks to Giacomo Raspadori's injury-time winner.

As Lazio dropped points yesterday, Napoli are now 17 points clear at the top of Serie A with just 7 rounds to go!

#JuveNapoli https://t.co/i9HpuPjyET

🇫🇷 | Team of the Week

Our brand new Ligue 1 TOTW is in! 👇

It was a weekend to remember for Lens — having recorded a 3–0 win over Monaco, they're the side represented by most players in our XI, while their star striker, Loïs Openda, is our Player of the Week. 🌟 https://t.co/2yYxi18dhZ

🇪🇸 | Team of the Week

With so many impressive attacking performances in LaLiga this weekend, we simply had to put together our TOTW as this quite offensive-minded 4-3-3! ⬇️

One man stands out among the rest of the field — Marco Asensio is our Player of the Week. 👑 https://t.co/Ajj547xWie

🇩🇪 | Team of the Week

Our highest-rated XI from this weekend's Bundesliga action is here! 🤩

Just six teams see their players featured in our Team this week, as Marvin Ducksch's perfect-rated performance against Hertha earned him our Player of the Week award. 🏅 https://t.co/0f8boL3Oas

🔎 | FOCUS

Ernest Poku (19) led AZ Alkmaar to a 5–0 win over Hajduk Split in the UEFA Youth League final with this excellent display:

👌 45 touches
⚽️ 2 goals
🎯 4 shots/3 on target
💨 4/7 successful dribbles
⚔️ 10/15 duels won
⚖️ 1 penalty won
📈 9.2 Sofascore rating

💫

#UYL https://t.co/oXJWp9Oc6Z

🇮🇹 | Team of the Week

Another round of Serie A action is now behind us, which means we have to unveil our latest TOTW! 👇

It was quite a tight race for our Player of the Week award, with several players particularly impressing, but ultimately it goes to Simone Verdi. 👏👏 https://t.co/CPARAGb6Na

📈 | HIGHEST-RATED PLAYERS

Before league action across Europe continues later today, it's time to show you our updated Top 10 in the Top 5! 🤩

Remarkably, all ten players occupy the same ten positions as last Tuesday, as Lionel Messi still dominantly holds the top spot. 👑 https://t.co/Rp9SxE5DiY

🔟 | PERFECTION

Valentin Castellanos v Real Madrid:

⏱️ 72' played
👌 15 touches
⚽️ 4 goals
🎯 6 shots/5 on target (1.61 xG)
👟 4/4 accurate passes
📈 10 Sofascore rating

The first player to put four goals past Los Blancos since Robert Lewandowski in 2013! 🔥

#GironaRealMadrid https://t.co/0dLAr3UJiO
